      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is a quick checklist for the crew to run through before climbing the scaffolding on the new residential build:\n\n1. **Base & Foundations**  \n   - Verify the scaffold base plates are level and fully seated on the foundation.  \n   - Check that the base plates are properly bolted or anchored to the ground or floor.  \n   - Inspect the base for any cracks, missing bolts, or loose fasteners.\n\n2. **Vertical Members (Posts & Tubes)**  \n   - Ensure all vertical posts are upright and aligned.  \n   - Confirm that all tubes are correctly inserted into the base plates and vertical posts.  \n   - Tighten all nuts and bolts to the recommended torque.\n\n3. **Horizontal Cross-Bracing**  \n   - Check that horizontal cross-bracing is installed at each level.  \n   - Verify that cross-bracing is properly tightened and aligned.  \n   - Inspect for any loose or missing braces.\n\n4. **Guardrails & Mid-Levels**  \n   - Install guardrails at the top and mid-levels.  \n   - Ensure guardrails are securely fastened to the horizontal cross-bracing.  \n   - Check the integrity of the guardrail connections.\n\n5. **",
